  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">English Language training for Expatriate Welfare Cell police in Sylhet</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Expatriate Welfare Cell operating in Sylhet, the ancestral home to majority of Bangladeshi origin British Nationals in the UK, specialises in offering police help and advice to all Bangladeshi ex-pats and provide assistance to over 500 British nationals per year. The Expatriate Welfare Cell will receive training on English Language to develop their language skills and identify new ways of working to provide better services to the British Nationals.</narrative>
